SAPL Node - Getting Started
===========================

This directory (/var/lib/sapl-node) is where the PDP looks for
.saplbundle files. The node is configured in BUNDLES mode with
signature verification enabled by default.

The node will not start until bundle security is configured.
You must either provide a signing key or explicitly allow unsigned
bundles before the service can run.


Quick Start (signed bundles)
----------------------------

1. Generate a signing keypair (one-time):

   sapl-node bundle keygen -o /etc/sapl-node/signing

   This creates signing.pem (private key) and signing.pub (public key).
   Keep the private key secure. The public key goes into the config.

2. Build and sign a bundle from the example policies:

   sapl-node bundle create -i /var/lib/sapl-node/example -o /var/lib/sapl-node/default.saplbundle -k /etc/sapl-node/signing.pem

3. Configure the public key in /etc/sapl-node/application.yml:

   io.sapl.pdp.embedded:
     bundle-security:
       public-key-path: /etc/sapl-node/signing.pub

4. Restart the service:

   sudo systemctl restart sapl-node

5. Verify:

   curl -s http://localhost:8443/actuator/health | jq .

   You should see "status": "UP".

The PDP watches this directory for changes. When you deploy a new
bundle, the PDP reloads automatically without a restart.


Writing Your Own Policies
-------------------------

Replace the example with your own policies:

1. Create a directory with your .sapl files and optional pdp.json
2. Build and sign: sapl-node bundle create -i ./my-policies -o /var/lib/sapl-node/default.saplbundle -k /etc/sapl-node/signing.pem
3. The PDP reloads automatically

See /var/lib/sapl-node/example/ for a starting point.


Disabling Signature Verification
---------------------------------

For development or evaluation, you can opt out of signature
verification. Add to /etc/sapl-node/application.yml:

   io.sapl.pdp.embedded:
     bundle-security:
       allowUnsigned: true

The node logs a warning on every startup when signature verification
is disabled. Do not use this setting in production.


